					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If it works, the greatness would depend a bit on how many times you would be able to multiplex it. If it's as good as per scanline, you might be able replace more than just one sprite with sprite 0 on a per 8px-row basis, depending the density of their content not overlapping. <br /><br />The bright dotted lines in the picture example posted above (rathergoodspr.png) could be rearranged to interfere as little as possible on a sliver basis, maybe realistically letting a per scanline-changing sprite 0 cover up to 3 or rarely even 4 such sprites in a single row.<br /><br /><br /><br />Here's another question that's ridiculous: <br />Has anyone tried writing to PPUCTRL to switch sprite mode mid-screen? This project *does* have pattern space to waste to accomodate both modes for one screen. The gain would be less rigid placement where needed, sprite conservation otherwise.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
